11 An Act relating to professions and occupations;
amending 59 O.S. 2021, Section 582, as amended by
12 Section 1, Chapter 252, O.S.L. 2023 (59 O.S. Supp.
2025, Section 582), which relates to the Board of
13 Examiners in Optometry; extending sunset date;
providing an effective date; and declaring an
14 emergency.
15
16
17 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
18 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 59 O.S. 2021, Section 582, as
19 amended by Section 1, Chapter 252, O.S.L. 2023 (59 O.S. Supp. 2025,
20 Section 582), is amended to read as follows:
21 Section 582. There is hereby re-created, to continue until July
22 1, 2026 2031, in accordance with the provisions of the Oklahoma
23 Sunset Law, the Board of Examiners in Optometry. This Board shall
24 consist of five (5) persons, four of whom shall possess sufficient
HB3004 HFLR Page 1
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 know ledge of theoretical and practical optics to practice optometry,
2 be duly licensed as optometrists, and who shall have been residents
3 of this state actually engaged in the practice of optometry for at
4 least five (5) years. The term of each licensed optometrist member
5 of the Board, one being appointed each year, shall be five (5)
6 years, or until a qualified successor is appointed. The lay member
7 of the Board shall serve a term coterminous with that of the
8 Governor and shall serve at the pleasure of the Governor. The
9 Governor is hereby authorized to appoint a member of the Board of
10 Examiners in Optometry at the expiration of any term or whenever,
11 for any reason, a vacancy may occur on the Board. Vacancies shall
12 be filled for the unexpired term only.
13 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective July 1, 2026.
14 SECTION 3. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
15 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
16 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
17 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
18
